                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Wow. Probably the best tasty Birria taco I've ever had in Fresno. Price is fair, maybe about 50 cents more expensive than when I get them in San Diego, but excellent quality.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   I just found this guy on Instagram, and decided to visit one of his pop up events. He was only serving tacos, which made my choice very easy. I order two tacos, and as the young woman that helped me said, regretted it after I started eating. There are some really delicious flavors here. First off, the meat is cooked perfectly tender without being overdone or under done. The flavoring is incredible. The consommé for dip is outstanding. There's a wonderful mix between spicy, and flavor throughout the entire taco, and the consommé. The salsa is a creamy green salsa that has a heavy citrus influence, with avocado and some nice heat. The salsa is ridiculously delicious; spicy in my opinion, but absolutely delicious and I wish I would've asked for more. The taco shells are perfectly crisp and what I would expect from this type of taco.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   All in all, this was absolutely delicious. I will definitely come back and grab more tacos in the future. Absolutely outstanding!
                  </span>
                 </p>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   We've been meaning to try this truck sooner, but our schedule's never lined up until one day, it did. I reached out on their IG to inquire about whether or not we should show up earlier than the opening time and they did suggest so, and what an accurate tip that was! There was consistently a line the entire time we were there (eating and all) and that speaks for itself. The line does, however, move very quickly and the gal running the register is excitable and interactive, especially if it's your first time there.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   We tried their birria ramen, tacos, and horchata. The birria ramen may look small, but there's surprisingly so much in it; very filling! Also loved their tacos and consome. The food was hot and satisfying.
                  </span>
                 </p>
                </div>

                <div class="css-9ul5p9">
                 <p class="comment__09f24__D0cxf css-qgunke">
                  <span class="raw__09f24__T4Ezm" lang="en">
                   Finally got a chance to give them a try tonight! Located on Shaw and Blackstone in front of Lifestyle Furniture Parking lot they opened at 5pm. We go there at 5:05pm and saw the line was already long. My husband stood in line while I waited in the car it too about 10mins for him to get to the front.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   We ordered 5 tacos, one burrito and one ramen. Literally 2 mins later as he came back in the car to sit away from the cold they called our order. They worked so fast. It was about a 12 mins ride back home. When I opened all the packaging the food was still nice and warm. Presentation looked great! The birria tacos came with the toppings, guacamole salsa and consomé. The ramen had all the toppings and sauce inside as well.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Everything was delicious! The tortilla was crunchy and the had so much flavor. The birria was good and so was the consomé. The ramen and burrito was also so yummy! Everything was so filling. And I loved their guacamole salsa.
                   <br/>
                   <br/>
                   Anthony's tacos definitely lives up to its hype! I've had birria tacos before and was never a fan but Anthony's tacos has "Wow-ed" me and definitely changed my mind. I will definitely be returning and I highly recommend them if you haven't tried.
                  </span>

       <div class="arrange__09f24__LDfbs gutter-2__09f24__CCmUo vertical-align-bottom__09f24__A9C03 css-174a15u">
        <div class="arrange-unit__09f24__rqHTg arrange-unit-fill__09f24__CUubG css-1qn0b6x">
         <h2 class="css-13merx8">
